Reasoning: 
- cs.RO (Robotics) is the most likely category as the paper deals with autonomous navigation of mobile robots in unknown and dynamic environments.
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is also likely as the paper discusses the use of a motion controller and verification of safety properties.
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is relevant as the paper discusses the use of a reactive potential field approach for collision avoidance.
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is less likely but still possible as the paper mentions the use of model predictive algorithms for collision avoidance.
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is also less likely but possible as the paper discusses the implementation of the proposed approach on a Pioneer P3-AT robot.
